text.tspan: SVG vs Canvas
Scalable Vector Graphics
Canvas
Each
graphical primitive is a DOM node
The
browser sees a canvas as a bitmap
, there is no
knowledge of the composing primitives
Scalable since each primitive is kept in memory
and can be scaled
Not scalable since only the bitmap will be scaled
High level API for events and styling = they rely
in DOM events and CSS like other nodes
Low level API, event handling at primitive level has to
be coded
Declarative and verbose = too many nodes imply
a lot of html code so longer downloading times +
more memory + longer time to display
Imperative (you tell how to draw not what to draw) =
more compact if many primitives + display time
depends on the js code not the number of primitives
